n{{Mexico-journalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=June 2011}}\n\n'''Jorge Fern\u00e1ndez Men\u00e9ndez''' is a [[Mexican people|Mexican]] [[journalist]].<ref name=\"Ferragut2007\">{{cite book|last=Ferragut|first=Sergio|title=A Silent Nightmare: The Bottom Line and the Challenge of Illicit Drugs|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DADb5Zgo3GkC&pg=PA273|accessdate=26 June 2011|date=May 2007|publisher=Lulu.com|isbn=978-1-4303-2944-2|pages=273\u2013}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n*Jorge Fern\u00e1ndez Men\u00e9ndez, a specialist in [[subversive]] movements has written the books: \n*Asesinato de un cardenal: ganancia de pescadores\n*El otro poder: Las redes del narcotr\u00e1fico, la pol\u00edtica y violencia in M\u00e9xico City\n*De los maras a los zetas: Los secretos del narcotr\u00e1fico de Colombia a Chicago\n*Nadie supo nada: La verdadera historia del asesinato de Eugenio Garza Sada\n*Calder\u00f3n presidente: La lucha por el poder\n\n===Radio work===\nJorge Fern\u00e1ndez Men\u00e9ndez has an important program in [[Imagen Radio|Imagen]] radio station located in 90.5 F.M. in [[M\u00e9xico City]] and also a TV program named \"nada personal\" in [[Proyecto 40]].\n\n==Awards & Recognition==\nIn 2000, Men\u00e9ndez was awarded the Premio Nacional de Periodismo, a national award of Mexico, for an editorial he wrote.<ref>{{cite web |title=Historia de \u201cPremio Nacional de Periodismo e Informaci\u00f3n\u201d (1975-2001) |url=http://www.periodismo.org.mx/Historia/cronologia_antes.html |website=Premio Nacional de Periodismo |accessdate=January 15, 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130203012556/http://periodismo.org.mx/Historia/cronologia_antes.html|archivedate=February 3, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fernandez Menendez, Jorge}}\n[[Category:Mexican journalists]]\n[[Category:Male journalists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{Mexico-journalist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jorge_Fern%C3%A1ndez_Men%C3%A9ndez"}
